cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR

The paper is about person re-identification using deep learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves learning representation of pedestrian appearance and exploiting semantic attributes, visual attention, and spatial dependencies among body parts, which suggests the use of machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) techniques. The approach also involves multi-task learning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of discriminative and robust pedestrian representation, which could be relevant to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
